                   <div class="video-container">\r\n                        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/4Ri5cszSKEg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <section class="post blog events isotope-item" style="position: absolute; left: 0px; top: 0px; transform: translate3d(10px, 426px, 0px);">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-5 medium-4 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2><a href="#" rel="bookmark" title="Letter to the Editor Discusses WellBeing Event at UNC-Chapel Hill">Letter to the Editor Discusses Quality of Life Measures Event at UNC-Chapel Hill</a></h2>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                    <div class="post-tags">events</div>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-6 large-offset-1 medium-7 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <time class="updated" datetime="2014-01-10" pubdate="">January 10, 2014</time>                \r\n                    <p>The Cape Fear Business News featured a review of the Quality of Life Measures event at UNC-Chapel Hill from one of the newspaper’s readers. Commending the… panel’s discussion on how to measure Quality of Life, the letter to the editor calls research within the Quality of Life Measures issue space a “fascinating and important new field of study.”</p>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <section class="post blog news isotope-item" style="position: absolute; left: 0px; top: 0px; transform: translate3d(10px, 697px, 0px);">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-5 medium-4 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2><a href="#" rel="bookmark" title="Press Release: Is it Possible to Measure Happiness and WellBeing? And What Role Should those Measures Play in Setting Public Policy?">Press Release: Is it Possible to Measure Happiness and Quality of Life? And What Role Should those Measures Play in Setting Public Policy?</a></h2>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                    <div class="post-tags">news</div>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-6 large-offset-1 medium-7 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <p>News content here</p>\r\n                    \r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n    </div><!-- end #main -->\r\n</div> <!-- end #content -->', 'Updates', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'updates', '', '', '2016-03-09 19:18:46', '2016-03-09 19:18:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/?page_id=232', 0, 'page', '', 0),
	(234, 1, '2015-03-05 03:09:42', '2015-03-05 03:09:42', '<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-your-quality-of-life-measures.jpg&#39;);">\r\n    <header>\r\n        <h1>Your Quality of Life Measures</h1>\r\n        <hr>\r\n    </header>\r\n</section>\r\n<div id="content" class="row">\r\n    <section class="post standard">\r\n        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h2>Your Quality of Life Measures</h2>\r\n                <hr/>\r\n                <p><span>This quiz represent a measure of your personal wellbeing. When completed it will result in four scores: a) your overall, objective wellbeing, b) your subjective wellbeing, c) the livability of your  life, and d) your lifeability.</span></p>\r\n                <p><span><strong>Explanation of terms:</strong></span></p>\r\n                <p><span><strong>Objective wellbeing</strong> refers to those factors that research have found to influence people’s wellbeing.</span></p>\r\n                <p><span><strong>Subjective wellbeing</strong> refers to your particular experience of your own life and represents your feeling of happiness and life satisfaction.</span></p>\r\n                <p><span>Your wellbeing emanates from the society in which you live and from your internal personal dynamics that enable you to benefit from that environment. The former refers to your livability and the latter to your Lifeability. In other words:</span></p>\r\n                <p><span><strong>Livability</strong> measures how the external, societal environment enables a person’s wellbeing.</span></p>\r\n                <p><span><strong>Lifeability</strong> measures an individual’s internal capacity to be happy and satisfied and his or her adeptness at taking advantage of the external environment.</span></p>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                [wp-simple-survey-1]\r\n            </article>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n</div>', 'Your Quality of Life Measures', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'your-quality-of-life-measures', '', '', '2016-03-18 18:25:51', '2016-03-18 18:25:51', '', 0, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/?page_id=234', 0, 'page', '', 0),
	(238, 1, '2015-03-05 03:15:10', '2015-03-05 03:15:10', '<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-getupdates.jpg&#39;);">\r\n    <header>\r\n        <h1>Get Updates</h1>\r\n        <hr>\r\n        </header>\r\n</section>\r\n	<div id="content" class="row">\r\n	    <section class="post standard">\r\n	        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n	            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n	                <h2>Stay Up to Date with the Quality of Life Measures</h2>\r\n	                <hr>\r\n	            </header>\r\n	            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n	                <form class="get-updates-form" method="post">\r\n	                    <div class="row clearfix form-field">\r\n	                        <div class="large-6 medium-6 small-12 columns">\r\n	                            <label><span class="required">*</span>Your Email:</label>\r\n	                            <input type="email" name="email" maxlength="50">\r\n	                        </div>\r\n	                        <div class="large-6 medium-6 small-12 columns">\r\n	                            <label><span class="required">*</span>Confirm Email:</label>\r\n	                            <input type="email" name="confirm_email" maxlength="50">\r\n	                        </div>\r\n	                    </div>\r\n	                    <div class="row clearfix form-field">\r\n	                        <label class="header light">Help us customize the information you receive for state-specific updates and local events:</label>\r\n	                            <div class="large-4 medium-4 small-12 columns">\r\n	                                <label>Country:</label>\r\n	                                <select name="country">\r\n	                                    <option value="AF">Afghanistan</option>\r\n	                                    <o